Dear Hiring Team, 

It is with great pleasure that I submit my candidacy for the Software Engineer position with American Airlines. I bring over three years of professional experience in full-stack development, cloud-native systems, and AI-driven solutions, along with a strong academic foundation as a Master of Science in Computer Science graduate from Pace University, NY.

Through my experience across two engineering roles, I have built and delivered production-grade systems that directly reflect the technical depth and operational excellence this position demands. As a Software Engineer at Sperse, I architected an integrated system translating natural-language intents into validated REST API calls across 1,000+ endpoints — requiring rigorous API contract design, input validation, and safe execution across distributed microservices. To ensure production reliability, I implemented a comprehensive observability stack using Langfuse and LangSmith with structured logging, tracing, and evaluation hooks for root cause analysis and performance measurement. Through architectural optimization applying object-oriented design and Agile methodologies, I reduced response time by 60% and API costs by 50%, directly addressing the scaling and latency challenges central to this role. Prior to Sperse, as a Software Engineer at Qualitest, I contributed to infrastructure that thousands of users rely on daily. I designed a cloud-agnostic Storage Service using Python, PostgreSQL, and Redis that seamlessly handled file operations across AWS S3, Google Cloud Storage, and MinIO via REST APIs with expiring signed URLs — giving me hands-on experience with cloud-native, multi-environment backend design. I also contributed to an Identity & Access Management platform built with React, Spring Boot, and AWS supporting thousands of users across 30+ applications, and developed workflows using AWS Step Functions and Lambda following DevOps Toolchain and CI/CD practices to handle long-running data imports. Together, these roles have prepared me to deliver high-quality work, solve technical problems, and build impactful components that enable cross-functional teams to deliver value at scale, speed, and reliability.

My academic research experience has given me a rigorous foundation in technical communication and mentorship — skills that translate directly into the collaborative culture and knowledge-sharing responsibilities this team values. As an AI Researcher at the Pace Artificial Intelligence Lab, I conducted applied research on StyleGAN and Stable Diffusion using CUDA, PyTorch, and LoRA on Pace University's HPC cluster, managing the full application lifecycle from training to deployment with vLLM and Hugging Face. Beyond building the systems myself, I led workshops on GPU programming with CUDA and Mojo, and on building AI Agents with LangChain and LangGraph, for an audience of 50+ students. Designing and delivering those sessions required me to break down complex technical concepts clearly and accessibly — directly mirroring the mentorship and knowledge-sharing responsibilities central to this role. This experience has shaped me into an engineer who builds with rigor and communicates with clarity, both of which I would bring to American Airlines' engineering team.

I have always been passionate about service excellence and building systems that care for people on life's journey, and I envision myself contributing my talent to furthering American Airlines' mission to provide world-class service and create an airline people love. I would love to discuss my interest in this position with your team and can be reached at #ph or #eml. Thank you for your time and consideration, I look forward to connecting!

